01
Strategic Overview
First time exhibiting at Wimmera. No history, no local recognition. The campaign needs to do the heavy lifting — build brand awareness from zero, put faces to the name, and convert foot traffic into qualified leads via a three-tier offer structure, each with its own QR code and landing page.
The Play

This is a 12-day campaign (23 Feb – 6 Mar) across three phases: Lead-Up, Event Days, and Post-Event. The cadence is daily but story-led — stories carry the daily presence while feed posts are reserved for high-impact moments that earn real engagement and shares. We're building awareness in a new region with no existing audience, so every feed post needs to land. Stories do the daily heavy lifting; the feed stays clean and meaningful.

The content arc follows a funnel: Awareness → Familiarity → Urgency → Conversion → Wrap-up. The giveaway (Milwaukee M12 Jacket) is the recurring hook that threads through every phase to give people a reason to engage even if they're not ready to talk nutrition yet. The jacket draw runs through the lead form — everyone who fills it in is automatically entered, so the giveaway drives data capture, not just foot traffic. On the final day, we'll use a digital wheel spinner (wheelofnames.com) to draw the winner live at the stand — a program manager spins it on-screen, and we film the moment for socials.

02
Offer Tiers
Three tiers, one lead form. Everyone who fills in the form gets something — the quality of the offer scales with the prospect's potential. This is smart because it means no one walks away empty-handed, and the form captures data regardless of tier.
High Potential
We Match Your 2026 Testing Investment
The big-ticket offer. For growers who are serious and have budget. Dollar figure based on 3 best opportunities — Bruce's call. This is a genuine value-match that positions Hybrid Ag as invested in the relationship, not just selling.
Trigger: Lead form completed + qualified high by team
Medium Potential
Nutritional Audit Service & Recommendation
The consultative offer. Lower commitment from the prospect, but still delivers tangible value. Positions the team as advisors, not salespeople.
Trigger: Lead form completed + qualified medium by team
Low / Warm Lead
Draw to Win a Milwaukee M12 Heated Jacket
The everyone-gets-a-go offer. Every form entry goes in the draw for the Milwaukee M12 Heated Jacket. Captures data from the curious, the tyre-kickers, and the "not yet but maybe" crowd. The jacket is the magnet — the form is the mechanism. No physical raffle box, no lost details.
Trigger: Lead form completed → entered in draw
QR Display Strategy

3 QR Offer Displays — created and being printed by Paige today. Each QR code links to its own landing page tailored to that tier. One QR display per tier with clear messaging about what they'll get. The "Low" tier display leads with the jacket — "Scan to enter: Win a Milwaukee M12 Heated Jacket." Place it near the entrance to capture everyone walking past. Place the "High" QR on the main table where Bruce and team will be having deeper conversations. James to collect with the brochures from Wang.

Three separate QR codes, three separate landing pages — each tailored to the offer tier. Every entry still goes in the jacket draw regardless of which QR they scan. Three pages, one pipeline.

Printed QR Offer Displays · Final Assets
High Tier · Match Testing
Medium Tier · Nutritional Audit
Low Tier · Jacket Giveaway
Giveaway Detail

Milwaukee M12 Heated Jacket — ordered in winner's size after the draw. Winner provides their size on the day (or via follow-up if they don't claim on-site). Drawn live on Day 3 (5th March) using a digital wheel spinner at wheelofnames.com — a program manager spins it on-screen at the stand and we film the moment for socials. No separate physical draw — entries from all three landing pages go into the spinner. This means every person who enters for the jacket is captured in the pipeline. The giveaway should be mentioned in every single post from 23rd Feb onwards. It's the recurring hook that drives form completions across all three tiers.
